---
import TopicLayout from '../../layouts/TopicLayout.astro';
const title = "Tools and Resources for Home Acoustic Analysis";
const description = "Discover acoustic measurement tools, software, calculators, and resources for analyzing and improving residential acoustics.";
---

<TopicLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Tools and Resources for Home Acoustics</h1>
  <p>Effective acoustic analysis and treatment requires appropriate tools ranging from smartphone apps to professional measurement systems. This guide covers essential resources for residential acoustic projects.</p>
  
  <h2>Measurement Microphones</h2>
  <p>Calibrated measurement microphones provide accurate frequency response for room analysis. Options range from affordable USB mics like the miniDSP UMIK-1 to professional-grade Earthworks M30s.</p>
  
  <h2>Analysis Software</h2>
  <p>Room EQ Wizard (REW) provides free comprehensive acoustic measurement and analysis. Essential for frequency response, waterfall plots, and impulse response analysis.</p>
  <p>Dirac Live offers advanced room correction with sophisticated phase and time-domain optimization.</p>
  
  <h2>Acoustic Treatment Products</h2>
  <p>Leading manufacturers include GIK Acoustics, Primacoustic, and Acoustimac. Products range from broadband absorption panels to specialized bass traps and quadratic diffusers.</p>
  
  <h2>Smartphone Apps</h2>
  <p>Mobile apps like Decibel X provide basic SPL measurement and frequency analysis suitable for preliminary assessment and educational purposes.</p>
  
  <h2>Educational Resources</h2>
  <p>The Master Handbook of Acoustics by F. Alton Everest remains the definitive reference. Online resources include the Acoustical Society of America and Home Theater Geek community forums.</p>
</TopicLayout>
